* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

00:51.985 --> 00:53.621
* NA-NA NA-NA NA *

00:53.687 --> 00:54.755
* NA-NA NA-NA NA *

00:54.822 --> 00:57.591
* NA-NA NA NA NA-NA NA *

00:57.658 --> 01:00.594
* NA-NA NA-NA NA
NA-NA NA-NA NA *

01:00.661 --> 01:04.265
* WHAT'S NEW,
SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:04.332 --> 01:06.200
* WANDER IN THE HIGHLANDS *

01:06.267 --> 01:08.236
* CRUISIN' TO THE FAIR *

01:08.302 --> 01:10.138
* WE'RE OFF TO
GLASBURGH CASTLE *

01:10.204 --> 01:12.240
* THEY SAY THERE'S
TREASURE THERE *

01:12.306 --> 01:14.408
* OH, GLASBURGH'S
NEAR AND YET SO FAR *

01:14.475 --> 01:19.280
* MY FEET HURT,
I WISH WE'D TAKEN A CAR *

01:19.347 --> 01:21.482
OOH, LOOKETH YON,
GOOD MINSTREL.

01:21.549 --> 01:24.318
THE CASTLE!
THE FAIR AWAITS.

01:28.289 --> 01:30.224
AH, THE FOG BE THICK
LIKE OUR HEADS.

01:30.291 --> 01:32.760
MAYHAPS WE SHOULD
CHILLETH FOR THE NIGHTETH.

01:36.530 --> 01:37.565
YO, YO, YO!

01:37.631 --> 01:38.832
WATCH THAT FIRE,
GOOD MINSTREL.

01:38.899 --> 01:40.401
THIS BE NOT OUR CRIB.

01:40.468 --> 01:43.204
WORRY NOT YOUR BAD SELF,
GOOD MINSTREL.

01:43.271 --> 01:45.939
THUS TOASTY BLAZE
IS TOTALLY UNDER--

01:46.006 --> 01:47.241
CONTROL!

01:53.914 --> 01:55.048
[ROARS]

01:55.115 --> 01:56.650
AAAH!
AAAH!

01:59.487 --> 02:01.789
[ROARS]

02:10.598 --> 02:13.267
LIKE, I CAN'T BELIEVE
WE CAME ALL THE WAY
TO SCOTLAND

02:13.334 --> 02:15.336
FOR A RENAISSANCE FAIR.

02:18.372 --> 02:20.708
GAVE ME AN EXCUSE
TO WEAR MY NEW
PEASANT BLOUSE.

02:20.774 --> 02:24.011
THE GLASBURGH FAIR'S
THE WORLD'S ONLY
RENAISSANCE FAIR

02:24.077 --> 02:26.079
HELD AT A REAL
MEDIEVAL CASTLE.

02:26.146 --> 02:29.583
IT'S TOTALLY AUTHENTIC.

02:29.650 --> 02:32.119
HEY, SCOOB,
AUTHENTIC MEDIEVAL
CHURROS.

02:32.186 --> 02:33.421
[SLURPS] YEAH!

02:33.487 --> 02:35.689
WOW! BEING A REAL
MEDIEVAL KNIGHT

02:35.756 --> 02:37.358
MUST HAVE BEEN AWESOME,

02:37.425 --> 02:39.193
JOUSTING AND WRESTLING--

02:39.260 --> 02:41.462
AND SLAYING
DRAGONS.

02:42.763 --> 02:45.466
Fred: BEWARE
THE GLASBURGH DRAGON.

02:45.533 --> 02:47.568
LIKE, OKAY, FRED.
GOT THE WARNING.

02:47.635 --> 02:49.803
SCOOB AND I WILL BE OVER
AT YE OLDE FOOD COURT.

02:49.870 --> 02:51.372
[CHUCKLES]

02:51.439 --> 02:53.374
* THEY SAY THERE IS
A TREASURE *

02:53.441 --> 02:55.609
* WITHIN
THE CASTLE WALL *

02:55.676 --> 02:57.611
* BUT NO ONE'S EVER FOUND IT *

02:57.678 --> 03:00.080
* AND LIVED
TO SOUND THE CALL *

03:00.147 --> 03:02.350
* FOR THOSE WHO SEEK
THEIR FORTUNE *

03:02.416 --> 03:04.418
* HAVE ONLY MET THE FLAME *

03:04.485 --> 03:06.487
* OF A THOUSAND-YEAR-OLD
DRAGON *

03:06.554 --> 03:09.156
* OL' GLASSIE IS HER NAME *

03:09.223 --> 03:12.159
GOSH, I WONDER IF
THAT'S A TRUE STORY.

03:12.226 --> 03:13.561
IT'S JUST A FOLK TALE.

03:13.627 --> 03:15.796
DRAGONS NEVER REALLY
EXISTED.

03:15.863 --> 03:18.432
[DRAGON GROWLS]

03:19.700 --> 03:21.935
ZOINKS!
THEN, LIKE, WHAT'S THAT?

03:25.339 --> 03:27.908
LIKE I SAID,
JUST A LEGEND.

03:27.975 --> 03:29.209
LEGEND, EH?

03:29.277 --> 03:31.779
DID A LEGEND
SINGE MY EYEBROWS
CLEAN OFF?

03:31.845 --> 03:32.880
WHY, JUST LAST NIGHT

03:32.946 --> 03:35.283
THE DRAGON BURNED UP
A LOCAL COTTAGE, HE DID.

03:35.349 --> 03:36.684
SEE FOR YOURSELF.

03:36.750 --> 03:39.219
THAT FOUL BEAST IS TRYING
TO RUIN MY FAIR.

03:39.287 --> 03:40.421
YOUR FAIR?

03:40.488 --> 03:42.956
AYE. THE NAME'S McEWAN.

03:43.023 --> 03:44.292
EWAN McEWAN,

03:44.358 --> 03:45.926
AND I OWN
THIS CASTLE, I DO.

03:45.993 --> 03:48.262
LOOKS LIKE YOU'VE
GOT A REAL MYSTERY
ON YOUR HANDS, SIR.

03:48.329 --> 03:49.797
IF YOU NEED ANY HELP--

03:49.863 --> 03:53.334
I DO NOT NEED HELP
FROM YOU ROWDY
HOOLIGANS.

03:53.401 --> 03:56.003
UH, UNLESS
YOU'VE GOT 5 SMACKERS

03:56.069 --> 03:59.707
FOR A PICTURE
WITH THE FEARSOME
GLASBURGH DRAGON.

03:59.773 --> 04:01.409
[GROWLING]

04:01.475 --> 04:03.744
UH, NO, THANKS.

04:03.811 --> 04:05.279
HEY, NOT SO FAST!

04:05.346 --> 04:07.648
YOU GOTTA WEAR A COSTUME
AT MY FAIR, LADY.

04:07.715 --> 04:10.050
WELL, I DO HAVE
A COSTUME, SIR,

04:10.117 --> 04:11.752
BUT IT'S NOT
EXACTLY ME.

04:11.819 --> 04:13.921
YOU SEE,
THE COSTUME SHOP
WAS OUT OF--

04:13.987 --> 04:15.423
I DON'T CARE!

04:15.489 --> 04:18.025
AND I'LL BE
RIGHT BACK.

04:21.895 --> 04:23.531
NOBODY SAYS A WORD

04:23.597 --> 04:25.933
AND NOBODY GETS HURT,
GOT IT?

04:28.736 --> 04:30.771
[GRUNTING]

04:33.106 --> 04:35.409
[PANTING]

04:35.476 --> 04:37.845
YOU GOTTA USE
YOUR LEGS, FRIEND.

04:43.250 --> 04:45.586
[GRUNTING]

04:48.956 --> 04:50.458
[PANTING]

04:50.524 --> 04:52.660
WHO KNEW THEY HAD
SUCH GOOD GOURMET FOOD

04:52.726 --> 04:54.862
BACK IN MEDIEVAL TIMES,
SCOOB?

04:57.197 --> 04:58.366
[GROWLS]

04:58.432 --> 05:00.934
AAAAH!
AAAAH!

05:02.736 --> 05:05.506
[GRUNTS]
I CAN BENCH 220.

05:05.573 --> 05:07.741
Shaggy and Scooby:
YAAAAAH!

05:10.243 --> 05:13.514
LIKE, WE SAW
THE REAL
SCARY DRAGON!

05:14.882 --> 05:17.551
SCARY, BUT DEFINITELY
NOT A REAL DRAGON.

05:17.618 --> 05:19.487
HUH? LIKE,
WHERE'D IT GO?

05:19.553 --> 05:22.823
YIII!
YIII!

05:22.890 --> 05:24.358
GUYS, COME BACK.

05:24.425 --> 05:26.994
IT'S NOT THE DRAGON.
IT'S JUST--

05:27.060 --> 05:28.396
[EXCITEDLY]
AAAAH!

05:28.462 --> 05:29.763
JAMISON STEVEN RIPLEY.

05:29.830 --> 05:31.031
WHO'S HE?

05:31.098 --> 05:34.702
HE WAS ONLY THE STAR
OF THE ROUNDTABLE GANG.

05:34.768 --> 05:36.704
THAT TEEN KING ARTHUR SHOW?

05:36.770 --> 05:39.473
WASN'T THAT CANCELLED,
LIKE, AGES AGO?

05:40.774 --> 05:43.511
EXCUSE ME,
MR. RIPLEY?

05:43.577 --> 05:46.480
WOULD YOU SIGN
MY LANCELOT
ACTION FIGURE?

05:46.547 --> 05:49.316
5 CLAMS FOR AN AUTOGRAPH.

05:49.383 --> 05:52.119
NAY, FAIR DAMSEL,
PUT AWAY THY LUCRE.

05:52.185 --> 05:53.387
LANCELOT GIVETH FREELY

05:53.454 --> 05:55.956
TO ONE WHO KEEPETH
MY EFFIGY.

05:56.023 --> 05:57.324
LANCELOT?

05:57.391 --> 05:59.793
IT WAS HIS CHARACTER
ON THE SHOW.

06:01.294 --> 06:03.296
WOW, THANKS.

06:03.363 --> 06:06.500
I'M A REALLY BIG FAN.

06:06.567 --> 06:08.268
OKAY, OKAY, MOVE ALONG.

06:08.335 --> 06:09.637
YOU'RE HOLDING UP
THE LINE.

06:09.703 --> 06:11.839
OH, BOY.
LIKE I CAN'T GET

06:11.905 --> 06:14.241
THAT SPOOKY DRAGON
OUT OF MY HEAD.

06:14.307 --> 06:15.709
FROZEN BANANAS?!

06:15.776 --> 06:18.412
HEY SCOOB, WHAT DO YOU SAY
WE SHOW THIS GUY

06:18.479 --> 06:20.481
OUR ULTIMATE JESTER
MAGIC ACT?

06:20.548 --> 06:22.750
REAH, REAH!

06:24.317 --> 06:25.619
WATCH IN AMAZEMENT

06:25.686 --> 06:29.657
AS WE MAKE THESE
FROZEN TREATS
DISAPPEAR!

06:34.895 --> 06:36.730
[MUNCHING]

06:36.797 --> 06:38.499
[WHISTLES]

06:41.535 --> 06:44.972
LET THE PUBLIC
HUMILIATION COMMENCE!

06:49.577 --> 06:51.712
LIKE, THIS IS
PUNISHMENT?

06:54.482 --> 06:56.584
HEY, HA HA HA!
COME BACK!

06:56.650 --> 06:58.552
WE DESERVE
TO BE PUNISHED.

06:58.619 --> 06:59.720
[DRAGON GROWLS]

06:59.787 --> 07:02.055
ZOINKS!
BUT NOT THAT MUCH!

07:02.122 --> 07:03.724
[ROARS]

07:07.928 --> 07:09.062
[WHIMPERING]

07:13.333 --> 07:15.435
LOOKS LIKE THIS IS
THE END, SCOOB.

07:17.104 --> 07:19.439
ONLY ONE THING
WE CAN DO.

07:21.308 --> 07:23.010
GOOD THINKING,
GUYS.

07:26.413 --> 07:29.149
WHAT A WASTE OF
PERFECTLY GOOD
KEBABS.

07:29.216 --> 07:31.451
[ROARS]

07:34.287 --> 07:36.557
WE'VE GOT TO DISTRACT
THAT THING!

07:36.624 --> 07:38.626
TOO BAD WE DON'T HAVE
A DAMSEL IN DISTRESS.

07:38.692 --> 07:41.862
DRAGONS ALWAYS GO FOR
A DAMSEL IN DISTRESS.

07:41.929 --> 07:42.963
OOF!

07:44.064 --> 07:45.465
[VELMA WHISTLES]

07:46.900 --> 07:49.469
I HAD TO OPEN
MY BIG MOUTH.

07:50.904 --> 07:52.072
[GASPS]

08:00.147 --> 08:01.481
[GRUNTING]

08:01.549 --> 08:03.016
[GROWLS]

08:03.083 --> 08:05.018
[ROARS]

08:05.085 --> 08:07.487
All: AAAH!

08:09.022 --> 08:10.490
AAAH!
AAAH!

08:15.328 --> 08:17.598
[GULP]
AAAH!

08:22.770 --> 08:24.938
[DRAGON ROARS]

08:25.005 --> 08:26.506
Fred: RUN!

08:39.486 --> 08:42.122
[ROARS]

08:46.827 --> 08:48.128
AAAAH!

08:49.162 --> 08:51.531
[ROARS]

08:58.305 --> 08:59.940
WHOAAH!

09:02.375 --> 09:04.945
[ALL BREATHING HEAVILY]

09:06.580 --> 09:09.216
HEY, WHAT ARE YOU
DOIN' BACK HERE?

09:09.282 --> 09:10.450
[WHIMPERS]

09:10.517 --> 09:12.820
LIKE--LIKE,
GETTING AWAY. DRAGON.

09:12.886 --> 09:14.421
I'LL SAY
YOU'RE DRAGGIN'.

09:14.487 --> 09:16.123
THE SHOW'S
ABOUT TO BEGIN.

09:16.189 --> 09:20.093
ALL CAST MEMBERS
ARE NEEDED AT
THE FEAST OF FOOLS.

09:20.160 --> 09:21.261
FEAST?!

09:21.328 --> 09:23.430
HA HA HA HA!
LIKE, WHY DIDN'T YOU
SAY SO?

09:23.496 --> 09:24.898
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND!

09:24.965 --> 09:26.366
THERE'S A HORRIBLE
MONSTER OUT THERE.

09:26.433 --> 09:27.635
THE FAIR'S IN DANGER.

09:27.701 --> 09:31.204
NICE TRY, GALAHAD.
LET'S GO.

09:34.541 --> 09:36.043
ONE FOR YOU...
[GULP]

09:36.109 --> 09:37.144
TWO FOR US.

09:38.145 --> 09:39.212
FIND ANY CLUES?

09:39.279 --> 09:40.280
NOT YET.

09:40.347 --> 09:41.782
BUT I'VE GOT A FEELING

09:41.849 --> 09:43.951
THERE'S MORE TO THIS DRAGON
THAN MEETS THE EYE.

09:44.017 --> 09:46.453
HEAR YE, HEAR YE.
[RINGS BELL]

09:46.519 --> 09:48.521
ALL HAIL THE KING
OF THE FAIR

09:48.588 --> 09:50.724
JAMISON STEVEN RIPLEY.

09:52.459 --> 09:54.327
[WHISPERS]
[SIGHS]

09:54.394 --> 09:58.098
I MEAN,
ALL HAIL LANCELOT,

09:58.165 --> 09:59.833
KING OF THE FAIR.

10:00.701 --> 10:02.703
[APPLAUSE AND CHEERS]

10:05.005 --> 10:06.774
AYE.

10:06.840 --> 10:09.209
UH, WOULD YOU LIKE ME
TO CUT THE CHEESE?

10:09.276 --> 10:11.311
I WAS SUPPOSED TO PLAY
THE KING THIS YEAR,

10:11.378 --> 10:14.648
THEN THAT TV FAKER SHOWS UP
AND STEALS MY PART!

10:14.715 --> 10:16.049
OH, LOOK AT HIM.

10:16.116 --> 10:18.218
[SARCASTICALLY]
HE'S SO AUTHENTIC.

10:18.285 --> 10:19.386
WHATEVER.

10:19.452 --> 10:21.321
WELL, BETTER LUCK
NEXT YEAR.

10:21.388 --> 10:23.623
AYE, IF THERE IS A NEXT YEAR.

10:24.892 --> 10:27.661
A FAIR DAMSEL
A MERE SERVANT?

10:27.728 --> 10:29.462
I THINK NOT.

10:29.529 --> 10:31.064
SERVING WENCH,

10:31.131 --> 10:32.465
TAKE THIS HENCE.

10:32.532 --> 10:33.834
SERVING WENCH?

10:33.901 --> 10:38.138
NOW, WHAT DOST MY LADY
REQUIRE FOR THINE FEAST?

10:38.205 --> 10:41.608
WOW! YOU REALLY
GET INTO YOUR CHARACTER.

10:41.675 --> 10:43.376
CHARACTER?

10:43.443 --> 10:45.245
[CROWD SCREAMS]

10:45.312 --> 10:46.379
Man: DRAGON!

10:46.446 --> 10:48.648
[ROARS]

10:56.857 --> 10:58.726
[SHAGGY WHIMPERS]

10:58.792 --> 11:00.627
[BOTH SHIVER]

11:00.694 --> 11:02.830
[ROARS]

11:18.145 --> 11:19.546
FOUL BEAST.

11:19.612 --> 11:21.048
I'LL SHOOT YOU YET.

11:21.114 --> 11:21.982
SHOOT IT?

11:22.049 --> 11:24.251
AREN'T DRAGONS,
LIKE, ENDANGERED?

11:24.317 --> 11:27.855
I WANT TO GET
A PICTURE OF IT FOR
NEXT YEAR'S FAIR BROCHURE.

11:27.921 --> 11:30.958
ATTENDANCE HAS DOUBLED
SINCE THAT THING SHOWED UP.

11:31.024 --> 11:34.361
SOMETHING ABOUT
THIS DRAGON BUSINESS
SURE SMELLS FUNNY.

11:34.427 --> 11:35.362
YEAH.

11:35.428 --> 11:37.230
[SNIFFS]
IT SMELLS LIKE--

11:37.297 --> 11:39.566
HELP! HELP ME!

11:39.632 --> 11:41.068
[GROANS]

11:44.905 --> 11:46.039
ARE YOU OKAY, FELLA?

11:46.106 --> 11:47.174
I THINK I WRENCHED
MY SHOULDER.

11:47.240 --> 11:48.976
I WAS SUPPOSED
TO JOUST

11:49.042 --> 11:51.879
AGAINST
JAMISON STEVEN RIPELY
TOMORROW NIGHT.

11:51.945 --> 11:53.747
NOW, I'LL HAVE
TO FORFEIT.

11:53.814 --> 11:54.748
FORFEIT?

11:54.815 --> 11:56.183
NAY,
GOOD SQUIRE.

11:56.249 --> 11:59.086
FORSOOTH, HERE'S
A WORTHY KNIGHT.

11:59.152 --> 12:00.253
COOL.

12:00.320 --> 12:02.722
[CROWD CHEERS]

12:04.958 --> 12:06.459
ARE YOU REALLY
UP FOR THIS, FRED?

12:06.526 --> 12:09.997
SURE. I TOOK
A JOUSTING CLASS
LAST SUMMER AT THE "Y."

12:10.063 --> 12:12.232
BESIDES, YOU DON'T USE
REAL LANCES.

12:12.299 --> 12:14.501
THEY'RE MADE
OUT OF PAPIER-MACH .

12:15.602 --> 12:17.204
THANKS.

12:17.270 --> 12:18.305
HYAH!

12:19.439 --> 12:22.009
[CROWD CHEERS]

12:24.444 --> 12:26.446
WOW! THAT'S
RUTHIE GIRL,

12:26.513 --> 12:28.715
RIPLEY'S HORSE
FROM THE ROUND
TABLE GANG.

12:28.782 --> 12:29.716
BIG DEAL.

12:29.783 --> 12:31.018
THEY FILMED
THAT STUPID SHOW

12:31.084 --> 12:33.253
DOWN THE ROAD AT
GLASBURGH STUDIOS.

12:37.390 --> 12:40.593
SHAGGY, YOU'VE STILL GOT
FRED'S JOUSTING ROD.

12:40.660 --> 12:42.529
LOOKS LIKE
HE FOUND
ANOTHER ONE.

12:42.595 --> 12:44.898
[CROWD CHEERS]

12:46.900 --> 12:50.070
Velma: THEY'RE USING
REAL LANCES.

12:50.137 --> 12:53.306
WHOA! LIKE,
CAN WE DISCUSS THIS?

12:53.373 --> 12:56.043
OOOHHHH!

12:56.109 --> 12:58.511
I GUESS THAT'S A "NO."

13:00.247 --> 13:01.314
OOHHHHH!

13:01.381 --> 13:02.349
AAH!

13:06.319 --> 13:07.220
HEY, SCOOB!

13:07.287 --> 13:09.289
I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU WERE IN THERE.

13:09.356 --> 13:10.557
Both: HUH?!

13:10.623 --> 13:12.259
Both: YIKES!

13:12.325 --> 13:13.460
Both: WHOA!

13:14.561 --> 13:15.896
[CRASH]

13:18.031 --> 13:19.799
SCOOBY AND SHAGGY
SAVED YOU GUYS.

13:19.867 --> 13:22.669
THOSE WEAPONS
ARE REAL.

13:22.735 --> 13:25.305
DOST THOU IMPLY
THAT VILLAINY IS AFOOT?

13:25.372 --> 13:26.373
I DOST.

13:26.439 --> 13:27.841
[CROWD GASPS]

13:29.642 --> 13:32.045
[ROARS]

13:47.995 --> 13:50.097
I HATE THIS DRESS.

13:50.163 --> 13:52.532
I CAN'T IMAGINE THIS
GETTING ANY WORSE.

13:52.599 --> 13:54.401
[ROARS]

13:59.439 --> 14:01.208
OKAY, IT GOT WORSE.

14:05.612 --> 14:07.214
[ROARS]

14:13.720 --> 14:14.654
DON'T WORRY, VELMA!

14:14.721 --> 14:15.956
WE'LL GET YOU
OUT OF THERE!

14:16.023 --> 14:18.058
THERE'S ONLY ONE THING
TO DO, GANG:

14:18.125 --> 14:19.192
BUILD A CATAPULT.

14:19.259 --> 14:21.094
QUICK. I'LL CUT DOWN
SOME TREES,

14:21.161 --> 14:23.863
AND YOU GUYS FIND SOME
GIANT RUBBER BANDS.

14:23.931 --> 14:25.265
UH, FREDDY.

14:27.500 --> 14:29.169
NOTE TO SELF:

14:29.236 --> 14:31.338
ORGANIZE A "DAMSEL
IN DISTRESS" UNION.

14:31.404 --> 14:34.241
THESE WORKING
CONDITIONS STINK!

14:35.275 --> 14:36.309
[GASPS]

14:38.378 --> 14:39.980
[SNIFFS]

14:40.047 --> 14:42.415
HMM.
THIS SMELLS FAMILIAR.

14:42.482 --> 14:45.218
"G.S.?" HMM.

14:46.453 --> 14:47.654
READY, GUYS?

14:47.720 --> 14:49.856
UH-UH.
NO WAY.

14:49.923 --> 14:51.558
Both: WHOA!

14:55.395 --> 14:58.365
I'LL TRY TO AIM
A LITTLE HIGHER
WITH YOU, DAPHNE.

14:58.431 --> 15:02.002
PERHAPS THIS WOULD BE
A LITTLE LESS MESSY?

15:04.071 --> 15:06.639
Fred: WELL, SURE.
WE CAN GO IN THE EASY WAY.

15:12.812 --> 15:15.949
WOW! CHECK OUT
THAT OLD TAPESTRY.

15:19.352 --> 15:21.989
[ROAR]

15:22.055 --> 15:24.157
OVER THERE.

15:26.893 --> 15:30.497
All: UHH! UHH! UHH!

15:30.563 --> 15:32.832
WRONG DOOR.
MY BAD.

15:32.899 --> 15:36.769
Fred: I DIDN'T KNOW
THEY HAD GYM EQUIPMENT
IN MEDIEVAL TIMES.

15:36.836 --> 15:38.972
HEY, LOOK.
IT'S VELMA'S HAT.

15:39.039 --> 15:42.209
AND A TOTALLY CUTE
LIZARD-SKIN PURSE.

15:42.275 --> 15:43.276
[GROWLS]

15:43.343 --> 15:44.277
OR NOT.

15:44.344 --> 15:46.413
[ROARS]

15:47.747 --> 15:49.449
All: AAH!

15:49.516 --> 15:51.518
[THE GHOST OF ME AND YOU
PLAYING]

16:02.162 --> 16:06.233
* I'VE BEEN DOWN *

16:06.299 --> 16:08.568
* WANDERING PAST
SECOND STREET *

16:08.635 --> 16:13.406
* AND LOOKING AT THE GHOST
OF YOU AND ME *

16:13.473 --> 16:17.010
* AND THINKING BACK
ON ALL THOSE MEMORIES *

16:17.077 --> 16:20.847
* OF HOW IT USED TO BE *

16:20.913 --> 16:25.852
* I'VE BEEN HEARING *

16:25.918 --> 16:27.487
* I HEAR THOSE VOICES *

16:27.554 --> 16:30.823
* ALL OF THE NOISES
OF BREAKING GLASS *

16:30.890 --> 16:34.061
* AND ALL THOSE
PLANS WE HAD *

16:34.127 --> 16:36.063
* TO GET US THROUGH *

16:36.129 --> 16:40.433
* AND THEY'RE NEVER
COMING TRUE *

16:40.500 --> 16:43.270
* AND I HOPE
AND I HOPE *

16:43.336 --> 16:45.705
* THAT YOU WON'T FORGET *

16:45.772 --> 16:47.840
* AND I'M HOPING,
HOPE YOU KNOW *

16:47.907 --> 16:52.179
* THAT I CAN CLEARLY SEE *

16:52.245 --> 16:57.417
* THE GHOSTS
OF YOU AND ME *

16:57.484 --> 17:00.753
* THE GHOSTS
OF YOU AND ME *

17:00.820 --> 17:02.855
[ROARS]

17:02.922 --> 17:08.228
* THE GHOSTS
OF YOU AND ME *

17:20.407 --> 17:21.341
[ROARS]

17:21.408 --> 17:23.176
AAH!

17:25.378 --> 17:27.347
LIKE, YOU GOT
ANY BUTTER, SCOOB?

17:27.414 --> 17:28.148
UH-UH.

17:28.215 --> 17:29.949
TOO BAD.
HA HA HA HA.

17:30.016 --> 17:31.951
'CAUSE IT LOOKS LIKE
WE'RE TOAST.

17:32.018 --> 17:35.388
[ROARS]

17:35.455 --> 17:36.389
[SNAPS TAIL]

17:36.456 --> 17:37.490
[SHIVERING]

17:38.491 --> 17:40.560
AHA.
CAREFUL, MY LADY.

17:40.627 --> 17:43.363
HE'S NOT GOING
TO HURT ME, ARE YOU, PUFF?

17:43.430 --> 17:45.698
NOT AS LONG AS I STAND
IN FRONT OF THIS TAPESTRY.

17:45.765 --> 17:48.935
SOMEONE WHO WANTED
THE TREASURE OF
GLASBURGH CASTLE

17:49.001 --> 17:51.838
WOULD NEVER BURN
THE TREASURE MAP.

17:51.904 --> 17:54.274
WHAT WOULD A DRAGON
WANT WITH TREASURE?

17:54.341 --> 17:56.343
THE DRAGON DOESN'T
WANT THE TREASURE.

17:56.409 --> 17:58.745
THE GOOD
SIR LANCELOT DOES.

17:58.811 --> 18:01.648
HUH? NO, UM--
MAKE HASTE!

18:01.714 --> 18:02.682
YOU'LL BE, UH,

18:02.749 --> 18:04.317
ROASTED ALIVE.

18:04.384 --> 18:06.486
YOU'VE BEEN USING
THIS HIGH-TECH
ROBOTIC DRAGON

18:06.553 --> 18:09.122
TO SCARE PEOPLE
AWAY FROM THE CASTLE

18:09.189 --> 18:11.724
SO YOU COULD
FIND THE TREASURE.

18:20.667 --> 18:22.635
UHH--WHOA--
WHOA!

18:24.904 --> 18:25.938
AAH!

18:26.005 --> 18:28.408
I DID IT, OKAY?
I DID IT!

18:28.475 --> 18:30.343
JUST GET ME
OUT OF HERE!

18:31.411 --> 18:33.580
LIKE, WHAT'S WITH
THE LIGHT SHOW?

18:33.646 --> 18:35.782
HIS MOTION-CONTROLLED
SUIT OF ARMOR

18:35.848 --> 18:37.116
IS SHORT-CIRCUITING.

18:37.184 --> 18:39.486
THAT'S HOW
HE CONTROLLED
THE DRAGON.

18:39.552 --> 18:42.755
IT WAS ALL LEFTOVER STUFF
FROM HIS TV SHOW.

18:42.822 --> 18:45.158
WHEN THE DRAGON BURNED
THE TENT AT THE FEAST,

18:45.225 --> 18:46.993
I THOUGHT I SMELLED
SOMETHING FUNNY.

18:47.059 --> 18:49.028
IT WAS KEROSENE.

18:49.095 --> 18:51.498
THAT'S BECAUSE
THE DRAGON'S FIRE

18:51.564 --> 18:53.466
CAME FROM
FLAMETHROWER TANKS,

18:53.533 --> 18:57.003
TANKS MARKED "G.S."
FOR GLASBURGH STUDIOS.

18:57.069 --> 19:00.240
BUT LIKE, WHY?
HE'S A BIG TV STAR.

19:00.307 --> 19:03.075
[SIGHS] AFTER MY SHOW
WAS CANCELLED,

19:03.142 --> 19:04.244
THE ONLY WORK
I COULD GET

19:04.311 --> 19:06.313
WAS THESE STUPID
RENAISSANCE FAIRS.

19:06.379 --> 19:07.580
I DESERVE
THAT TREASURE.

19:07.647 --> 19:10.450
I MEAN, PLEASE,
I'M LANCELOT.

19:10.517 --> 19:12.151
[LAUGHS]
I'D HAVE GOTTEN IT, TOO,

19:12.219 --> 19:14.254
IF NOT FOR YOU MEDDLING
MEDIEVAL KIDS!

19:18.124 --> 19:19.058
OOPS.

19:19.125 --> 19:20.760
[GASPS] THE MAP!

19:20.827 --> 19:21.961
YOU FOOL!

19:22.028 --> 19:23.696
UH, WHO'S THE FOOL,
RIPLEY?

19:23.763 --> 19:26.433
THAT MAP WAS
A CROCK OF HOOEY.

19:26.499 --> 19:29.402
I MADE UP
THE LEGEND OF
THE GLASBURGH DRAGON

19:29.469 --> 19:31.271
TO ATTRACT TOURISTS.

19:31.338 --> 19:33.573
I EVEN SHAVED OFF
ME OWN EYEBROWS

19:33.640 --> 19:36.142
AND CLAIMED THE DRAGON
TORCHED THEM.

19:36.209 --> 19:38.711
[LAUGHS]

19:46.586 --> 19:49.956
ALL HAIL THE NEW KING
OF THE FAIR...

19:50.022 --> 19:52.859
SHANE FLINTY!

19:52.925 --> 19:55.728
[CROWD CHEERS]

19:59.699 --> 20:02.402
LIKE, IMAGINE
THE VEGGIE KEBAB
WE COULD MAKE

20:02.469 --> 20:04.537
WITH THAT SKEWER,
EH, SCOOB?

20:07.274 --> 20:08.241
Both: OH!

20:08.308 --> 20:10.477
HEY, SCOOBY
AND SHAGGY

20:10.543 --> 20:12.512
PULLED THE SWORD
FROM THE STONE.

20:12.579 --> 20:14.747
WELL, SURE.
THERE'S 2 OF THEM.

20:16.849 --> 20:17.950
SCOFFLAWS!

20:18.017 --> 20:20.787
THAT SWORD
IS THE PROPERTY
OF THE NEW KING.

20:20.853 --> 20:23.055
* AND SO THE TALE
HAS COME TO A CLOSE *

20:23.122 --> 20:24.857
* THE DRAGON'S A PHONY
WITH GAS IN ITS NOSE *

20:24.924 --> 20:29.996
* THE MYSTERY WAS SOLVED
BY A RENAISSANCE CREW *

20:30.062 --> 20:33.800
* AND SO GOES
THE LEGEND OF *

20:33.866 --> 20:36.703
* SCOOBY-DOOBY-DOO *

20:36.769 --> 20:38.305
[LAUGHS]
